<br>
Then there is the fact that if the melee has no wands to use and no lev you can kite him forever because you can protect your buffs with jboots + any other insta cast item and you'll be pretty much immune to melee dmg.<br>
<br>
Then you have to add your skin spell, which will either take time to pumice off or time to wear through.<br>
<br>
If he golem wands you outdoors yonder off and rebuff.  He'll have to fight you without golem wands shortly.  He can't burn that pp forever.<br>
<br>
I would tend to think that with thurg quest and similar quality gear with ac hp mr pr gear you could get to 2000 hp counting mannaskin at mid 50s easily. <br>
<br>
For fighting a rogue I would point out that you only need about 1300 manna.  You also only need to maintain 90pr for an even con and hopefully 100 mr as a just in case sort of thing.  I suggest after that is atained all gear you equip go to increasing ac and hp as those are the only things that will matter in the fight.<br>
<br>
I think that outdoors its very viable for you to force a rogue into a losing position.  This often wont result in death for the rogue as they can flee but then you can yonder, gate, or zone many times too.<br>
<br>
Indoors its another matter.  If you get attacked by a rogue indoors I recommend you gate.  If you initiate the attack chances are your gonna either exploit los or lose.  I suggest indead hitting the rogue with one nuke zoning out and fighting him outdoors if he follows.<br>
<br>
